title: Grateful Dead Live at Boston Garden on 1994-10-02
lineage: Dat (Tascam DA-20) -> Tascam DA-3000 -> Samplitude Professional v11.2.1 -> FLAC/
description:
Set 1

Jack Straw, Loser, It's All Over Now, Row Jimmy, Broken Arrow, Mama Tried*-> Mexicali Blues*, Tennessee Jed, Picasso Moon

Set 2

Iko Iko, Samba In The Rain, If The Shoe Fits, Samson & Delilah, Crazy Fingers-> Truckin'>, That Would Be Something-> Jam-> Drums-> Space-> The Days Between-> Throwing Stones-> Not Fade Away, E: U.S. Blues

* Weir on acoustic guitar

reviews.review_text:
Fall '94 Boston N5: Twenty-Ninth Days Between 29/41: 29/41: TWBS (8:14) -> Drumz -> (20:43) -> Days Between (12:42) -> Throwing Stones -> NFA.

Sunday night show that is too hard to follow 10/1. I would honestly skip this one, though please do indulge in the forty minutes from That Would Be Something through drumz to The Days Between. Definite high point of the night.

I am on an amazing journey I am listening to every 1994 show in order, mining for gold. 

Hard to follow a show like 10/1/94 at this stage of the game, but this one is still enjoyable. 

Set 1 Highlights: All songs played well, but nothing extraordinary. 

Set 2 HIGHlights. Truckin', Space>Days Between. Space is like one long Days intro here. Fairly strong performance of Throwing Stones here too.
